{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8fb72788-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2407"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2407"},"text":"§ 2407.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Special authorization for use of foreign currencies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1306"},"text":"section 1306 of title 31","children":[],"tail":", the President is authorized, as a demonstration of good will on the part of the people of the United States for the Polish and Italian people, to use foreign currencies accruing to the United States Government under this chapter or any other Act, for assistance on such terms and conditions as he may specify, in the repair, rehabilitation, improvement, and maintenance of cemeteries in Italy serving as the burial place of members of the armed forces of Poland who died in combat in Italy during World War II."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8fb72789-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 648, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/633"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–633","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 303, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-10-07"},"text":"Oct. 7, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/1014"},"text":"78 Stat. 1014","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8fb7278a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8fb7278b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id8fb7278c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-04"},"text":"Sept. 4, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/424"},"text":"75 Stat. 424","children":[],"tail":", known as the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2151"},"text":"section 2151 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id8fb7278d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1306"},"text":"Section 1306 of title 31","children":[],"tail":"” substituted in text for “section 1415 of the Supplemental Appropriation Act, 1953, ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s724"},"text":"31 U.S.C. 724","children":[],"tail":"]” on authority of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1067"},"text":"96 Stat. 1067","children":[],"tail":", the first section of which enacted Title 31, Money and Finance."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id8fb727